🐘 4. The Kind Elephant

In a jungle, there lived a big elephant named Raju. Though he was strong, he was also very kind.

One hot day, a small bird cried, “My nest fell! My eggs are on the ground!”

Raju carefully picked up the eggs with his trunk and placed them safely back in the tree.

Another day, a group of ants struggled to cross a stream. Raju gently placed a leaf as a bridge so they could cross.

The animals loved Raju, but some thought kindness was a weakness.

One day, a storm hit the jungle. Trees fell, and animals got trapped. Raju used his strength to clear paths and rescue them.

Now everyone understood — kindness was not weakness, it was strength.

The animals thanked Raju, and he smiled happily.

From then on, many animals started helping each other, just like Raju.

Moral: Kindness is the greatest strength.